@startuml
title TPL Architecture - Backend Component Boundaries

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
hide methods
hide stereotypes

package "Transport Layer" {
  class Routers
  class AuthDependencies
  class SchemaContracts
}

package "Application Layer" {
  class FeatureServices
}

package "Domain/Persistence Layer" {
  class DomainModel
  class Database
}

Routers --> AuthDependencies : guard/authz
Routers --> SchemaContracts : request/response validation
Routers --> FeatureServices : delegate workflows

FeatureServices --> DomainModel : business rules + persistence orchestration
DomainModel --> Database : ORM mapping

note right of Routers
Intent:
- Keep routers transport-thin
- Avoid router business orchestration
end note

note right of FeatureServices
Intent:
- Cross-entity workflows and invariants
- Reusable domain operations
end note

note right of DomainModel
Intent:
- Persistence entities and relations
- No router-layer dependencies
end note

@enduml
